There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
The record is active in the system

This process will delete the current journey logs and regenerate them based on the starting times and dates in the Aircraft records.
Recalculate and generate the aircraft journey logs.

The aircraft journey logs are not manually updateable. Entries are added as flightsheet entries are made and each journy log entry has a list of the associated flights. The Aircraft Airframe time is set according to the last log entry. The log can be generated using the "Generate Journey Logs" process. Opening airframe times are taken from the Aircraft tab of the Fleet Maintenance window. The airtimes of the journey log can be recalculated using the process "Update Journey Logs".
Aircraft Journey Logs record the flight activity of the aircraft in the fleet.
